<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="92" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="92">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="92">This species is named after the famous Puerto Rican singer Jennifer Lopez.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="93" pageId="3" pageNumber="92" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="92">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="93" pageId="3" pageNumber="92">
Six 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1925" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litarachna" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="93" start="start">Litarachna</pageBreakToken>
</taxonomicName>
species have their first coxal plates fused, i.e., 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1925" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litarachna degiustii" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="degiustii">Litarachna degiustii</taxonomicName>
Cook, 1958 (Caribbean Sea - 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, DR" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of The Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="7" pageNumber="96" pagination="19 - 22" title="A new species of Litarachna from the British West Indies (Acarina: Pontarachnidae)." volume="60" year="1958">Cook 1958</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V" journalOrPublisher="Cahiers de Biologie Marine" pageId="7" pageNumber="96" pagination="253 - 259" title="Marine water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia: Pontarachnidae) from the Caribbean Sea, with description of one new species." volume="49" year="2008">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1925" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litarachna amnicola" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amnicola">Litarachna amnicola</taxonomicName>
Cook, 1986 (Tasmania - 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, DR" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute" pageId="7" pageNumber="96" pagination="1 - 568" title="Water mites from Australia." volume="40" year="1986">Cook 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" pagination="53 - 62" title="New records of water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia) from Tasmania, with descriptions of three new species." volume="2070" year="2009">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
and Smit 2009
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1925" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litarachna brasiliensis" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">Litarachna brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
Smit, 2007 (Brazil - 
<bibRefCitation author="Smit, H" journalOrPublisher="Systematic and Applied Acarology" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" pagination="141 - 146" title="Litarachna brasiliensis n. sp., the first member of the water mite family Pontarachnidae (Acari: Hydrachnidia) from South America." volume="12" year="2007">Smit 2007</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1925" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litarachna caribica" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caribica">Litarachna caribica</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
, Chatterjee &amp; Schizas, 2008 (Caribbean Sea - 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V" journalOrPublisher="Cahiers de Biologie Marine" pageId="7" pageNumber="96" pagination="253 - 259" title="Marine water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia: Pontarachnidae) from the Caribbean Sea, with description of one new species." volume="49" year="2008">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1925" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litarachna indica" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">Litarachna indica</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
, Chatterjee &amp; Ingole, 2012 (West Indian coast - 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V" journalOrPublisher="Cahiers de Biologie Marine" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" pagination="547 - 553" title="A new species of Litarachna Walter, 1925 (Acari: Hydrachnidia) from the West Indian Coast, with a discussion on the diversity of the family Pontarachnidae Koenike, 1910." volume="53" year="2012 a">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2012a
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1925" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litarachna minuta" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">Litarachna minuta</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
, Chatterjee &amp; Marshall, 2013 (Brunei Darussalam - 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2013).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="93">
Due to the glandularium-like structure fused with posterior margin of Cx-IV, 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1925" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litarachna lopezae" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lopezae">Litarachna lopezae</taxonomicName>
sp. n. most closely resembles to 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1925" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litarachna minuta" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">Litarachna minuta</taxonomicName>
, a species known from a single female from Brunei Bay, but differs by a pair of small platelets with coxoglandularia 4 and associated setae lying free in the integument, not fused with Cx-IV (fused in 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1925" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litarachna minuta" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">Litarachna minuta</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="93">
Moreover, peg-like seta at the base of P-4 ventral projection separates new species from 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1925" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litarachna minuta" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">Litarachna minuta</taxonomicName>
and other species with fused first coxal plates.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="93" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="93">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="93">
The mites were collected from 69.5 m depth. The greatest depth at which pontarachnid mites have been recorded previously was reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" pagination="63 - 67" title="A new species of Pontarachna (Acari, Hydrachnidia, Pontarachnidae) from a mesophotic coral ecosystem off Vieques Island, Puerto Rico, Caribbean Sea." volume="3440" year="2012 b">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
et al. (2012b)
</bibRefCitation>
who found 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Pontarachna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pontarachna nemethi" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nemethi">Pontarachna nemethi</taxonomicName>
in a mesophotic coral ecosystem near Vieques Island of Puerto Rico at 67 m depth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="93" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="93">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="93">Only known from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
